The Soviet state, back in the late 1950s, tried to rectify the situation,
instructing to create and put into production a truly “people's car.” This was supposed to be the Zaporozhets. For this, the former Zaporozhye combine plant was converted, which became the Zaporozhye automobile plant Kommunar. class, did not suit. After analyzing the current situation, the government, chaired by Kosygin A.N., proposed building a new automobile plant that could produce over half a million cars a year and thus satisfy the demand of the population for a personal vehicle.